#month-banner("Three", "Two", "Via Humida: The Wet Path into Mineral Work", "The dissolving medium meets the mineral kingdom — One full cycle completed")

#v(0.8em)

#hm-note[
  Month 2 establishes the fundamental operative rhythm of Year Three: the
  dissolution-evaporation-salt recovery-cohobation cycle. The student will
  repeat this cycle many times throughout Year Three. The first cycle is
  the most important for building perceptual sensitivity — what does this
  mineral look like in solution? What do its crystals reveal? What happens
  at the first cohobation? Document everything in this first cycle; later
  cycles will be compared against it.

  Monitor students for the common error of moving to the next cycle before
  the first is fully observed and recorded. The Long Way cannot be properly
  observed if it is hurried.
]

